Deprecated API

Contents

  • Interfaces
  • Classes
  • Methods
  • Interfaces 
    Interface Description
    software.leonov.common.base.BinaryFunction
    This interface is the legacy version of BiFunction. It has been refactored to extend BiFunction for backwards compatibility. Java 8+ users should use to BiFunction directly.
    software.leonov.common.base.BinaryPredicate
    This interface is the legacy version of BiPredicate. It has been refactored to extend BiPredicate for backwards compatibility. Java 8+ users should use to BiPredicate directly.
  • Classes 
    Class Description
    software.leonov.common.base.Checksums
    Users not working with legacy APIs should prefer Guava's Hashing facility.
    software.leonov.common.base.MessageDigests
    Users not working with legacy APIs should prefer Guava's Hashing facility.
    software.leonov.common.collect.SkiplistSet
    This class should only be used for testing. It provides no practical benefit when compared to java.util.TreeSet and lacks navigation methods defined in the NavigableSet interface.
    software.leonov.common.collect.TreeBasedSet
    This class should only be used for testing. It provides no practical benefit when compared to java.util.TreeSet and lacks navigation methods defined in the NavigableSet interface.
    software.leonov.common.util.Dates
    Java 8+ users should switch to the new Date and Time API.
  • Methods 
    Method Description
    software.leonov.common.base.BinaryPredicates.and​(BinaryPredicate<? super T, ? super U>, BinaryPredicate<? super T, ? super U>, BinaryPredicate<? super T, ? super U>...)
    Use BiPredicate.and(BiPredicate) instead.
    software.leonov.common.base.BinaryPredicates.or​(BinaryPredicate<? super T, ? super U>, BinaryPredicate<? super T, ? super U>, BinaryPredicate<? super T, ? super U>...)
    Use BiPredicate.or(BiPredicate) instead.
    software.leonov.common.base.Obj.hashCode​(Object)
    Java 7+ users should switch to Objects.hashCode(Object) instead.
    software.leonov.common.base.Obj.toString​(Object)
    Java 7+ users should switch to Objects.toString(Object) instead.
    software.leonov.common.collect.Iteration.in​(Iterator<T>)
    Jave 8+ users can create an Iterable from an Iterator using Java's lambda facility, for example: 
     for (final String s : (Iterable<String>)() -> iterator) {
    ...
 }
    software.leonov.common.io.ByteStream.getChecksum​(InputStream, Checksum)
    Users not working with legacy APIs should prefer hash(InputStream, Hashing.crc32()).padToLong() or hash(InputStream, Hashing.adler32()).padToLong() which uses Guava's Hashing facility.
    software.leonov.common.io.ByteStream.getDigest​(InputStream, MessageDigest)
    Users not working with legacy APIs should prefer ByteStream.hash(InputStream, HashFunction) which uses Guava's Hashing facility.
    software.leonov.common.io.Fs.getChecksum​(File, Checksum)
    Users not working with legacy APIs should prefer hash(File, Hashing.crc32()).padToLong() or hash(File, Hashing.adler32()).padToLong() which uses Guava's Hashing facility.
    software.leonov.common.io.Fs.getDigest​(File, MessageDigest)
    Users not working with legacy APIs should prefer Fs.hash(File, HashFunction) which uses Guava's Hashing facility.
    software.leonov.common.io.MappedFileInputStream.available()
    Use MappedFileInputStream.remaining() instead.

    software.leonov.common.io.Zip.close​(ZipFile, boolean)
    Java 7+ users should switch to try-with-resources or Guava's Closeables.close(Closeable, boolean) instead.
    software.leonov.common.io.Zip.closeQuietly​(ZipFile)
    Java 7+ users should switch to try-with-resources or Guava's Closeables.close(Closeable, boolean) instead.
    software.leonov.common.io.Zip.getEntries​(ZipFile)
    Java 8+ users should prefer ZipFile.stream(). If an Iterator is required users can call Stream.iterator().
    software.leonov.common.util.Numbers.nextRandomInt​(int, int)
    Java 8+ users should use ThreadLocalRandom.nextInt(int, int) or SplittableRandom.nextInt(int, int).
